# Three storage shapes

Pick the **shape of access** before the service — three categories, **not interchangeable**.

## Object — S3

Files over **HTTP**, scales to infinity, **no filesystem** semantics. The centre of gravity of AWS storage.

## Block — EBS / Instance Store

A **virtual disk** for one machine, random block I/O. **EBS** (durable, network-attached) · **Instance Store** (local, ephemeral).

## File — EFS / FSx

A **network filesystem** many machines mount at once. **EFS** (Linux/NFS) · **FSx** (Windows, Lustre…).

**The category is the decision** — wrong shape = nothing fits; right shape = the rest is tuning.
